import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    ax = sns.scatterplot(x="population", y="engineers", data=data)
    ax.set(xlabel='Population', ylabel='Engineers')
    plt.title('What is the correlation between the population and number of engineers in each state?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    ax = sns.barplot(x="state", y="engineers", data=data, palette="Blues_d")
    ax.set(xlabel='State', ylabel='Percentage of Engineers')
    ax.axhline(y=data['engineers'].max(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Max Percentage of Engineers: {:.2f}'.format(data['engineers'].max()))
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.legend(loc='upper left')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='hurricanes', kde=False, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['hurricanes'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.axvline(data['hurricanes'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of the number of hurricanes that have hit each state?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Number of Hurricanes')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
